I was thinking about how humans have a big advantage compared to mixed diurnal/nocturnal animals, because they get to be fully protected from nighttime stress through full night sleep, while some animals have to suffer parts of the night awake due to the predation cycle

Like during summertime you can literally go to bed with the sunset and wake at dawn, perfectly covering the night period of darkness and staying protective from nighttime's pro-aging effects. Lots of organisms cannot afford to do this. There's wolves lurking, prey to catch, etc.

The Internet basically fulfills all the failed promises of multiculturalism. You can tweet about some local folk tradition and an Indian bro will respond that they have something similar 5000 km away. You can order a barrel of moringa oil and have it delivered. It's wonderful imo
